@NODE "Distribution" "Distribution"

 Photoware
 ---------

 'Odin' is photoware. It means that if you use it more than 1/500th second a
 day you HAVE TO send @{" me " Link "Contact"} picture of yourself (have mercy and make it <10kb ;-)


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

 Installation
 ------------

 Please, read carefully. 'Odin' can (an probably will) crash your machine
 when installed improperly.

 * First of all you have to copy the contents of @{b}'bin'@{ub} drawer into your
   @{b}'Thor/bin'@{ub} directory.
 * Then, copy the @{b}'pics'@{ub} directory into @{b}'S:'@{ub} (this is preferred location, you
   can choose another one -- see @{" Configuration " Link "Configuration"}).
 * Finally, copy the contents of @{b}'rexx'@{ub} drawer wherever you want.

 OK, we can start Thor now. Go to configuration window and choose
 'Global' --> 'Arexx Scripts'. You ended up with 'Arexx scripts' window just
 in front of you, right? Lets select our newly copied scripts:
  * for 'Entering Confs' -> odin_start.rexx
  * for 'THOR Quit' -> odin_stop.rexx

 Save your settings and quit Thor. Now it's time for @{" Configuration " Link "Configuration"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 Introduction
 ------------

 Perhaps you know how monotonous reading mail can be. This is an attempt to
 somewhat enlive it by adding possibility of showing picture of mail's
 author. In a window on specified public screen. Using datatypes. Wow!


@ENDNODE

@NODE "SystemReq" "System Requirements"

 System requirements
 -------------------

 * Any Amiga capable of using datatypes will do.

 Tested on
 ---------

 * A4000/040, OS3.0, Picasso96

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Configuration" "Configuration"

 Configuration
 -------------

 There are three things you can configure:

  * window position
  * pictures path
  * name of the public screen Odin's window will be opened on

 If you are a good boy (girl) and folowed installation guide carefully,
 AND (which is very important) you're running Thor on its OWN screen you
 may start Thor now and enter any conference which has unread messages in
 it...click.....click....Wow! It works!

 Now, you, bad, bad boy. You, considering yourself an expert. You never follow
 any guidelines, eh? You copied 'pics' into 'dh1:comms/mail/thor/data/decoded'
 and you're running Thor on your 1600x1200 Workbench screen, right? That's too
 bad. You'll have to edit 'odin_start.rexx'.

 Try to find the under-mentioned line:

 @{fg highlight}"run >nil: `GetEnv THOR/THORPath`bin/Odin 553 35 s:pics/ Thor.1"@{fg text}
                                            |  |     |      |
 X coordinate of the left top corner--------+  |     |      |
                                               |     |      |
 Y --------------------------------------------+     |      |
                                                     |      |
 Pictures path (note the ending slash) --------------+      |
                                                            |
 Public screen name ----------------------------------------+


@ENDNODE

